  nlc COMMAND
  nlc [COMMAND] --help | -h
  nlc --version | -v

[1mCommands:[0m
  [32mrun[0m             Run a natural language command (default)
  [32mconfig[0m          Manage configuration
  [32mconfig show[0m     Show configuration and environment
  [32mconfig clear[0m    Delete the config file (falling back to default values)
  [32mconfig edit[0m     Edit the configuration file (create it first if needed)
  [32mconfig new[0m      Create a new config file
  [32mprompt[0m          Manage system prompt
  [32mprompt system[0m   Show or edit system prompt
  [32mprompt user[0m     Show or edit user prompt
